Package net.sf.jclec.mo.evaluation.fitness

Fitness definition package.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ICrowdingDistanceMOFitness
    This interface specifies the methods that the fitness of a solution should provide if the strategy is based on the crowding distance computation.
    IGrEAMOFitness
    This interface defines the methods that the fitness of a solution should provide if the strategy use some of the procedures defined by the GrEA algorithm.
    IHypercubeMOFitness
    This interface defines the methods that fitness object should implement to store information about the hypercube an individual belongs to.
    INSGA2MOFitness
    This interface defines the methods that the fitness of a solution should provide in order to use some of the procedures defined by NSGA-II algorithm.
    INSGA3MOFitness
    This interface defines the methods that the fitness of a solution should provide in order to use some of the procedures defined by NSGA-III algorithm.
    IPAESMOFitness
    This interface defines the methods that the fitness of a solution should provide in order to use some of the procedures defined by PAES algorithm.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GrEAMOFitness
    Additional fitness properties of a solution for the GrEA strategy.
    HypercubeMOFitness
    Hypercube properties of a solution.
    MOFitness
    Fitness for a multi-objective problem.
    NSGA2MOFitness
    Additional properties of a solution for the NSGA-II strategy.
    NSGA3MOFitness
    Additional properties of a solution for the NSGA-III strategy.
    OMOPSOMOFitness
    Additional properties of a solution for the OMOPSO strategy.
    PAESMOFitness
    Additional properties of a solution for the PAES strategy.
